<TITLE> Ex-law secy Awal moves to JS secretariat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 22 (bdnews24.com)  Former law secretary Kazi Habibul Awal has been posted to the parliament secretariat. The transfer comes in the wake of the High Court's order on Feb 1 declaring Awal's appointment as law secretary illegal. The establishment ministry issued a notice on Monday ordering transfers in a number of top civil servant postings. Awal replaces Ashfaq Hamid who has been transferred to the ministry of religious affairs. Abdur Rob Hawlader, acting secretary at the ministry of religious affairs, has been made acting secretary of the science ministry. Secretary of the science and ICT ministry AKM Abdul Awal Majumder has been made chairman of the Land Reform Board on deputation. Additional secretary at the law ministry Shahidul Haque has been made secretary in charge of the legislative drafting and parliamentary affairs division of the same ministry. Joint secretary Gyan Ranjan Shil, who was officer on special duty (OSD) at the establishment ministry, has been appointed a member of the Bangladesh Export Processing Zone Authority (BEPZA) on deputation. bdn
